    "body": "## Purpose\n\nWhen `VLLM_USE_DEEP_GEMM=0` is set when using `FLASHMLA_SPARSE`, `is_deep_gemm_supported` will be False but we will still call `fp8_paged_mqa_logits`. This causes a crash when using DeepSeek V3.2 since it will read `is_deep_gemm_supported` as False and the uninitialized/stale schedule metadata will be used by `fp8_paged_mqa_logits`.\n\n## Testing\n\n```\nVLLM_USE_DEEP_GEMM=0 vllm serve nvidia/DeepSeek-V3.2-NVFP4 -tp 4\n```\n\npreviously crashes but is now stable. Manual debugging and logging confirmed the source of the crash as the stale metadata, and I was able to reproduce an IMA in the deepgemm_attention test script if I use the same stale metadata tensor that was seen during inference.\n",
    "created_at": "2026-02-23T04:10:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-02-24T23:09:22Z",
